<p>Among the winners of the night, Paul Thomas Anderson&rsquo;s <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/hollywood/one-battle-after-another-exclusive-leonardo-dicaprio-on-his-dream-collaboration-with-benicio-del-toro-and-their-camaraderie-1396785">Leonardo DiCaprio</a>-led&nbsp;<a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/reviews/one-battle-after-another-review-leonardo-dicaprio-presents-value-for-money-hilarity-with-punch-in-the-gut-emotion-1397201">One Battle After Another</a> was the biggest earner with an impressive 6 grabs. Michael B. Jordan&rsquo;s Sinners followed with 3 of its own. Robert Aramayo, who led I Swear,&nbsp;was the most welcome surprise, winning the coveted Best Leading Actor award among some of the best contenders.&nbsp;</p>

<p>However, the biggest shock remained Marty Supreme, which was given no trophies even after being in the running for a whopping 11. The Josh Safdie sports dramedy tied 1969 film Women in Love and 2004&rsquo;s Finding Neverland in doing so. The latter two went on to nab one Oscar each, meaning all hope is not lost for the <a href="https://www.pinkvilla.com/entertainment/hollywood/timothee-chalamet-goes-instagram-official-with-kylie-jenner-after-dating-for-3-years-tremendously-grateful-1399867">Timoth&eacute;e Chalamet</a> starrer, which did get big wins at Critics Choice Awards and the Golden Globes.</p>

